en: Shellfish collected by children are most easily identified by variety and size, Keegan said. Child foragers tend to be generalists, meaning that they're more likely to collect small shells indiscriminately. This research suggests that small, easy to transport and low-yield mollusks found in high amounts on a site indicate the presence of child foragers, he said.
zul: Ama-shellfish aqoqwa izingane kuvame ukuba lula ukuwahlonza ngokohlobo nobungako, kusho uKeegan. Abadobi abayizingane bavame ukubheka okujwayelekile, okusho ukuthi maningi kakhulu amathuba okuthi baqoqe amagobolondo amancane ngaphandle kokukhetha. Uthe, lolu cwaningo lusho ukuthi izinkovu ezincane, okulula ukuzithutha nezinenzuzo encane ezitholakala ziziningi kakhulu endaweni ziveza ukuthi bekukhona abadobi abayizingane.
mt0: U-Keegan uthe i-shellfish eqoqwe izingane ezazitholakala kalula ngokuhlukahluka kanye nesize, uthe. I-child foragers usually umuntu othile, okusho ukuthi umuntu othile uthola izinhlanzi ezincane ngokungeziwe. Le ncwadi ibonisa ukuthi i-small, elula ukuhambisa, kanye ne-low-yield mollusks ekhona endawo ebonisa ukuthi i-child foragers ikhona, uthe.

en: The production of sperm -- otherwise known as spermatogenesis -- generates more than 1,000 sperm per second in normal males. This productivity comes, in part, from a special cell type called the spermatogonial stem cell. The staying power of this stem cell has allowed many celebrities, including Robert DeNiro and Pablo Picasso, to father children after the age of 65.

Lokhu kukhiqiza kwenzeka, njengengxenye, kuvela kuhlobo lweseli olukhethekile olubizwa nge-spermatogonial stem cell. Amandla okuhlala ale stem cell avumele ukuthi inqwaba yosaziwayo, okubandakanya uRobert DeNiro noPablo Picasso, babe woyise bezingane beneminyaka engama-65.
mt0: Ukwenza i-sperm - okuthiwa ngokuthi spermatogenesis - generates i-sperms engaphezu kuka-1,000 per second in a male. en: Today, those using Planck and cosmic background data to obtain a value for the Hubble constant get a figure of 67.4 plus or minus 0.5. en: Unlike cryptocurrencies such as bitcoin, nifties are cryptographic tokens that represent a unique asset or good on the blockchain, are one of a kind, and are not interchangeable. Blockchains can enable gamers to buy and trade interoperable digital collectibles such as skins, dances, and in-game items, helping further fuel a $50 billion-plus annual market1 for virtual goods.

Ama-blockchain angenza abadlali bathenge futhi bahwebe ngezinto ezisebenza ngobuchwepheshe bedijithali ezoqoqekayo njengama-skin, abadansi, nezinto zemidlalo, okusiza ukuqhubeka nokufaka isamba esingaphezu kwezigidigidi ezingu-$50 ezimakethe maqondana nempahla yezobuchwepheshe ephakathi kumakhompyutha.
mt0: U-Niftiyi uhlukile e-bitcoin, i-Niftiyi i-cryptographic token ebonisa i-asset noma i-good ehlukile e-blockchain, i-one of a kind, futhi ayishintshi. en: "For me, it was a feeling of, 'I knew I could do this, and now I've done it'. I believed it could be done, so it was nice to confirm that.
